<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 13 at 4:56PM MDT until July 13 at 9:00PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 515 PM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN MADISON COUNTY...
At 456 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 20 miles southwest of Bozeman to 7 miles south of
Ennis, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Virginia City, Ennis, Norris, Jeffers, Cameron and Mcallister.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
